{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Recreating This Section for Your Online Brand
    Transform the physical-store layout into a premium online-first experience with two parts: the main headline and the two-column booking section.
    
    Part 1: Main Headline
    
    Pre-Headline: Small, all-caps, letter-spaced accent font.
    Example: A PERSONALISED EXPERIENCE
    
    Main Headline: Primary large sans-serif font. Replace store links with your services.
    Example: Book a <a href="#">virtual consultation</a>, get expert style advice, and find your perfect pair with our <a href="#">home try-on</a> service.
    
    Part 2: Booking Section ("Virtual Store")
    
    Left Column (Invitation)
    
    Pre-Headline: All-caps accent font.
    Example: EXPERT ADVICE AWAITS
    
    Headline: Standard smaller bold headline font.
    Example: Book a Virtual Consultation
    
    Paragraph: Explain value and ease of a virtual appointment.
    Example: "Get one-on-one time with our expert stylists from the comfort of your home. We'll help with fit, measurements, and curate frames perfectly suited to your features and style."
    
    CTA Buttons:
    
    Primary solid black: BOOK A CONSULTATION →
    
    Secondary outline: EXPLORE HOME TRY-ON
    
    Right Column (Visual)
    
    Use an image representing your online service.
    Example: A professional, welcoming photo of a stylist on a laptop screen, with an out-of-focus home try-on kit in the foreground.
    
    Contain the image in a sharp-cornered rectangle consistent with brand style.
    
    Final Summary
    This section converts a store-focused layout into a powerful online invitation, highlighting expert help and frame selection from home. The design is clean, premium, and fully aligned with New Vantage Co.’s modern, online-first brand identity.
{% enddoc %}
